# Trivy ignore file — list of vuln / misconfig / secret rule IDs to suppress.
# One ID per line. Comments start with `#`.
#
# Add an entry only after triaging the finding via upstream docs / source.
# Mirror the rationale in security/SECURITY.md (Trivy exceptions table).
#
# Examples:
#   CVE-2023-12345   # accepted: only triggers in non-default config
#   AVD-KSV-0014     # accepted: see SECURITY.md row

# --- libraw23t64 in nextcloud:latest debian 13.4 base ---
# 18 rows. No fixed version available upstream as of 2026-05. Will resolve
# when nextcloud:latest rebases against a debian point release that backports.
CVE-2026-20884
CVE-2026-24450
CVE-2026-24660

# --- mesa GPU userspace bundled in frigate:stable-rocm debian 12 base ---
# 38 rows. Unfixed in debian 12; frigate hasn't rebased to debian 13.
CVE-2026-40393

# --- ffmpeg in frigate + jellyfin upstream images ---
# 46 rows. Upstream image refresh cadence; not actionable from the homelab side.
CVE-2026-40962

# --- sqlite3 in frigate / immich-ml / immich-postgres / pgvector debian 12 ---
# 5 rows. Unfixed in debian 12; will clear when the upstream images rebase.
CVE-2025-7458
